email.body:
Hi!
For some days I noticed that the gtk widgets hangs when 
opening a webiste in a browser by using system() and START 
under windows.
It just hangs when there is still a browser window opened.
If no window is opened it will work fine.
The problem definitfly isn't because of system(), pipes 
and shell executes are producing the same error, but in 
batch-files, with c shell execute or using the command.com 
it works.
After aborting the execution of php the links gone to be 
opened in webbrowser.
I think it isn't a gernal problem with callbacks, because 
by testing this with a gtk timeout it works fine. It only 
happens on callbacks of buttons and similar widgets.

I'm using windows 2000 and the Firefox webbrowser.
The settings of Firefox when getting in this trouble are 
simply "Open new links in a new tab".

A friend of mine confirmed the error.

Here is some code producing this error (In combination 
with described webbrowser settings)
<?php
dl('php_gtk');

//Creating a button with calback to "website"..
$button = &new GtkButton('Google');
$button->connect('clicked', 'website');

//Creating a window..
$box = &new GtkHBox();
$box->add($button);

$window = &new GtkWindow();
$window->connect_object('destroy', 
array('gtk','main_quit'));
$window->add($box);
$window->show_all();

//The website function which starts google.com in default 
webbrowser..
function website()
{
   system('start http://www.google.com');
   return TRUE;
}

//Starting main loop..
gtk::main();
?>

I didn't test it using Opera with tabbed browsing yet, but 
this might interesting.

Any ideas?
