PHP-GTK Development Mailing List (http://gtk.php.net/)
To unsubscribe, visit: http://www.php.net/unsub.php

main_ext.txt prevents Zend from trying to load extensions we don't have in
place (yet).  We could probably get away with libglade, but there's not much
point at present.

main_except.txt uses something that's actually available via the Zend API ;)

gtk_zts.txt is just ZTS fixes (not too many here).

I still get heaps of warnings - not a huge problem, doesn't break anything,
just prevents a pure build - from the declaration of STYLE_NUM_STATS as uint
on line 166 of php_gtk+_types.c.  Making it 'int' clears those warnings -
could it break anything else to make that change?

I'm likely to complete work on the basic win32 build system tomorrow...
that's not including the generator, but does include a bunch of new files.

Will do a fresh checkout following these commits and make sure I didn't miss
anything ZTS-related before I finish up.

- Steph (gone for beer)






