-- PHP-GTK Development Mailing List (http://gtk.php.net/) To unsubscribe, visit: http://www.php.net/unsub.php

No, connect_replace() would *not* act like connect_object(). It would 
substitute user-specified object instead of the signal one, e.g.:

$drawarea->connect_object('button_press_event', 'process_object', 
$anotherarea);

function process_object($event, $anotherarea)
{
	/* note that $anotherarea is passed after event */
}

$drawarea->connect_replace('button_press_event', 'process_replace', 
$anotherarea);

function process_replace($anotherarea, $event)
{
	/* note that $anotherarea is passed in place of the signal widget */
}

And also I'm curious, why do you need connect_object() or 
connect_replace()? Any specific reason?

-Andrei


