Been mucking about with C again.

This works on my box, but I'm not sure how you'll feel about the
implementation Andrei, the lack of technical know-how notwithstanding.

I've made all the parameters optional so you can just call $menu->popup();
in any kind of callback and it'll give the default 'at the mouse pointer'
positioning.  The hard part was getting positioning to work at all when it
was given, but it's picking up the user callback properly now (here at
least).

Pls adv,

- Steph

ps Did you come to any decision about making use_underline = true the
default in menuitem/button constructors?  I've a small patch for that
sitting here too.

