Well, I'm pretty sure I know how it _should_ work....

<?php

/* working */
$window = new GtkWindow();
$window->connect_object('destroy', array('gtk', 'main_quit'));
$window->realize();

/* apparently working */
$drawable = $window->window;
$gc = $window->style->white_gc;

/* apparently not working, but not throwing errors either */
$drawable->draw_rectangle($gc, true, 4, 4, 580, 340);

/* working */
$window->show_all();
gtk::main();

?>

Then again, I haven't tried drawing on an expose event yet.  Perhaps if
someone tries to update the Scribble demo, we'll know more.

