Hi , this almost works , but since I am mostly a copy and paste artist , 
I really dont get whats up here ....

the below works , but only if the passed array is even in number .. e.g

	$dialog->set_authors( array('Pinky','And', 'The', 'Brain' ) ) ;
works fine, but
	$dialog->set_authors( array('Pinky', 'And' ,'The', 'Brain', 'doh') ) ;
segfaults ?
whyfor ??

I am sure it is something to do with this...

list = g_new( gchar *, len++ ) ;

which I do not think is doing what I thought itwas doing since the other 
problem is that the array needs to have at least 4 elements or it 
segfaults ~ BUT if I call set_artists() with an array of 4 strings THEN 
call set_authors() with just 2 strings then its ok ... set_artists & 
set_authors are essentially the same code only with different names.

e.g
$dialog->set_authors( array('Pinky' ,'And' ) ) ;
$dialog->set_artists( array('Pinky' ,'And' ,'The' , 'Brain' ) ) ;
segfaults , but
$dialog->set_artists( array('Pinky' ,'And' ,'The' , 'Brain' ) ) ;
$dialog->set_authors( array('Pinky' ,'And' ) ) ;
is fine


/**************************************************/
static PHP_METHOD(GtkAboutDialog, set_authors)
{

	int len, i=0;
	zval *php_list, **item;
	const gchar **list;

	NOT_STATIC_METHOD();

	if (zend_parse_parameters(ZEND_NUM_ARGS() TSRMLS_CC, "a/", &php_list) 
== FAILURE ) {
		return;
	}

	len = zend_hash_num_elements(Z_ARRVAL_P(php_list));
	list = g_new( gchar *, len++ ) ;
	zend_hash_internal_pointer_reset(Z_ARRVAL_P(php_list));
	while (zend_hash_get_current_data(Z_ARRVAL_P(php_list), (void 
**)&item) == SUCCESS) {
		convert_to_string_ex( item ) ;
		list[i++] = Z_STRVAL_PP( item ) ;
		zend_hash_move_forward(Z_ARRVAL_P(php_list)) ;
	}
	gtk_about_dialog_set_authors( GTK_ABOUT_DIALOG(PHPG_GOBJECT(this_ptr)), 
list ) ;
	g_free(list);

}
/**************************************************/

