Andrei Zmievski wrote:

> We're not going to wrap gtk_signal_* funcs automatically. Besides, they 
> are deprecated. But I've been adding relevant methods to GObject actually.

I found this in the phpg_gobject.c file. Is this one of the relevant 
methods? If so, can I just call it with $widget->block($signalHandlerId)?

static PHP_METHOD(GObject, block)
{
     guint handler_id;

     NOT_STATIC_METHOD();

     if (!php_gtk_parse_args(ZEND_NUM_ARGS(), "i", &handler_id)) {
         return;
     }

     g_signal_handler_block(PHPG_GOBJECT(this_ptr), handler_id);
}

