Hi,

during development with GtkTreeView and GtkTreeStore I ran into a 
problem with the signals row-expanded/test-expanded-row [1]. When 
they're getting actived php exits with:

Fatal error: Cannot instantiate abstract class GBoxed in <filename> on 
line 11. The line is always the Gtk::main() call.

Short example (requires my latest patches):

<?php
$w = new GtkWindow;
$s = new GtkTreeStore(Gtk::TYPE_STRING);
$i = $s->append(null, array("a"));
$s->append($i, array("b"));
$t = new GtkTreeView($s);
$t->append_column(new GtkTreeViewColumn("", new GtkCellRendererText, 
"text", 0));
$t->connect("row-expanded", create_function("", ""));
$w->add($t);
$w->show_all();
Gtk::main();
?>

cheers,
- Markus

[1] 
http://developer.gnome.org/doc/API/2.0/gtk/GtkTreeView.html#GtkTreeView-row-expanded

