Hi all,

I'd like to kill off gtk_color_button_new_with_color() completely (put it in
the ignores) and instead have GdkColor as an optional param in the
GtkColorButton constructor.

I have a trivial patch to make GtkColorButton::get_color() work in the
expected manner too.

With both patches in, this test script currently works on my laptop:

<?php

function test_this($cb) {
 $color = $cb->get_color();
 var_dump($color);
}

$window = new GtkWindow();
$window->connect_simple('destroy', array('gtk', 'main_quit'));

$color = new GdkColor();
$red = $color->parse("red");

//$cb = new GtkColorButton($red); // either construction works
$cb = new GtkColorButton();
$cb->connect('clicked', 'test_this');
$window->add($cb);

$window->show_all();
gtk::main();

?>

Anyone have strong feelings for/against this?

- Steph

